    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="999"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d999">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.922/101a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Siam</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 3, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Department’s No. 26 of November 2, 5 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>] p.m.
                    Following correction for Article 3 of treaty.</p>
                <p>Article 3 unchanged except following paragraph is in substitution for original
                    sixth and seventh paragraphs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“If either High Contracting Party establishes or maintains, directly or
                            indirectly, any form of control of the means of international payment,
                            it shall in this respect apply to the other High Contracting Party the
                            most-favored-nation treatment.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The fifth paragraph of the protocol repeated in telegram No. 26 of November 2 is
                    correct but please substitute “last paragraph” for “seventh paragraph”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
